Norwich City have suspended two supporters from attending matches at Carrow Road while the club and police investigate claims of racial abuse during their Sky Bet Championship clash against Wolves last Sunday.

The Norfolk club have also promised to hand out lifetime bans to any supporters found guilty of racist behaviour.

Norwich received numerous complaints from supporters following an incident in the visiting end at Molineux as the Canaries lost 1-0 in their first competitive match since relegation from the Barclays Premier League.

